yet, excited for where God will take me on this next chapter of my life. We opened the tearoom in 2012 , being told we would never make it by selling tea and making reservations. Not too mention we were tucked away on a little corner on a side street. But, God had a plan!!After 6 months of renovations we opened our first location on west Fort Dade in Brooksville, after not even 2 years of being up and running we were asked to move our business to the old Rogers Christmas House .So off to night and day of renovations yet again on a much larger scale. It took 7 months with the help of my family to completely rewire, replumb,redo all the original wood floors , walls and most ceilings . Yet, we managed to open for our busiest season. The business continued to be blessed with growth. Just as the first house became my home away from home so did this one. You see when you renovate a house like that, you pour everything you have into it. It becomes you ,in an essence . Your style and your personality. At the end of 5 years there ,our lease was up .... I went through a major storm in my life and didn\u2019t know if the tearoom could or would continue. I left it in God\u2019s hands. Then came my miracle! I was able to purchase the building literally across the street to make into \u201cthe new home of the tearoom \u201c. Soooo yet again , it was time for my family to get their work clothes out again and the renovations began . We opened in November  almost 2 years ago ! This tearoom as most of you know has and is my heart. I have been so blessed to have the opportunity to fulfill my dream. For me it was always about serving each of you with a warm heart and a smile. It is more than just tea; it\u2019s about the experience. I have met so many wonderful people through owning this business. Blessings right and left .. Friends that are like my family to me now. I feel like as if I have been writing my own story. So many wonderful memories that I could share. With every book , there are chapters. Some that you love and some that you might want to forget. Yet , as you continue it is always taking you to that next chapter. You remember something from each one. For me, I am ready to experience the \u201c next chapter\u201d in my story. My husband, has had job opportunities that will cause us to relocate. He is a critical care nurse. With a year of covid , he is exhausted. He is ready for a change. I wish I could be in two places but, I can\u2019t. So I am reaching out to those of you that know me personally . It would mean the world to me to find that right person that would love this tearoom as much as I have. I want these memories to continue for so many people that love coming here and have supported me in this journey. I am not quite sure when this new job will take place but, I would like to be prepared for when it does happen. Someone that I could set them up to succeed and continue forward with The Tilted Teacup Tearoom;)If you are interested please message me privately... I haven\u2019t been able to see so many of you as since we reopened from the covid closure , I am now back running my kitchen to create all the yummy treats for you \ud83d\ude09 I love you all and ask that you would keep myself and my family in your
